<TITLE> Coasts back on alert with depression over Bay </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 27 (bdnews24.com)Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla ports have been advised to hoist local cautionary signal-3 as a depression was developing over the Bay of Bengal, a Met office weather bulletin said Monday. All fishing boats and trawlers over the north Bay were advised to seek shelter till further notice, as squally weather looks likely to hit coastal regions of Bangladesh
